reviewText: Quite boring and drab.  The movie dragged on and often gave any enlightened information on the topic.  Poor presentation and I wouldn't recommend this movie either for entertainment or insight.
Title: Hillary Uncensored! An American Above The Law

reviewText: What this documentary shows is that Hillary Clinton is guilty of being party to illegal fundraising for her Senate campaign of 2000. It demonstrates that she has no problem with breaking campaign finance laws, if doing so benefits her, as long as the media doesn't find out about it, and she isn't held accountable. She's shown breaking campaign finance laws, lying about it, and attempting to cover it up. This makes her a weaker candidate on the campaign reform issue compared with either Mc Cain, or Obama. Although McCain is even now trying to break or bend the laws he once helped establish. None of this is surprising as the Clintons have a reputation for being relentless power grabbers. It's important to note that there is nothing partisan about this documentary, it is based on footage shot by a former Clinton fundraiser, who was used then tossed away like a piece of garbage when he became a political liability. It raised questions for me regarding Hillary's character, her inability to be truthful, and accountable for her actions, two traits i despise about our current president.
Title: Hillary Uncensored! An American Above The Law

reviewText: From the first moment this documentary starts, they try to tell you that it is supposed to be non-partisan. How can one man's story not be partisan?It does provide some interesting facts that suggests that Hillary may have violated campaign financing law. I just couldn't follow the entire trail due to either bad editing, or the director just wanted to make it as hard to follow as possible.Would I recommend this to my friends and family? Probably not, Hillary, and Bill are doing enough to destroy her campaign. I don't think this hard to follow documentary has much impact on that. Also by trying to pass this off as non-partisan, when you can clearly tell it's a partisan vendetta documentary makes all the claims suspect in my opinion.
Title: Hillary Uncensored! An American Above The Law

reviewText: I'm not a Hillary fan, or a Clinton fan in general.  From the description i expected something with some meat in it.  This was just an empty burger bun.  There is nothing substantive here.  What is described as the terrible injustices here are something that hundreds if not thousands of other politicians  have done and will continue to do, despite the laws that were written to prohibit it.  If this were so awful, why wouldn't the Bush administration, FBI, DOJ have started an investigation with an "independent" Ken Starr type?  Monicagate, Whitewater etc are more "scandalous.  If you used the rules/laws indicated in this piece, all of Congress, K Street and every state in the nation would be backlogged with court cases.  Sorry.
Title: Hillary Uncensored! An American Above The Law

reviewText: This movie brings it all back home.  Watch it and remember why America breathed a sigh of relief when those two grifters left the Whitehouse, pardoning terrorists and stealing furniture.Remember Billy Dale?How dare we forget..."Those who forget the past are doomed to relive it...."
summary: You always forget the pain and remember the good times.
Title: Hillary Uncensored! An American Above The Law

reviewText: I usually don't care much for documentaries but this one is exceptionally well done and I would recommend it to anyone interested in politics.
Title: Hillary Uncensored! An American Above The Law
